free: #e A child caught a frog.
#c 一個小孩捉了一隻青蛙。
#e He put it in a container.
#c 他（把牠）裝在一個瓶子裡。
#e At that night, the child went to sleep.
#c 晚上了，小孩睡了。
#e The frog escaped stealthily from the container.
#c 瓶子..不, 是青蛙偷偷的逃走了。
#e (He) got up in the morning, and see...
#c 他早上起來看到..
#e He saw that the frog had escaped.
#c 他看到青蛙逃走了
#e They looked for the frog (everywhere) inside the house. They turned every container over and looked for (the frog).
#c 他們在房子裡面找, 他把很多容器翻過來找。
#e He thought (the frog) was inside (of the containers).
#c 他們以為青蛙在那些容器裡面。
#e His dog inserted its head inside the container where the frog had been.
#c 他的狗把牠的頭塞進原來裝青蛙的瓶子裡面。
#e (He) didn't see the frog inside.
#c 他沒看到青蛙在裡面。
#e He headed out of the window and called the frog.
#c 他把頭往窗外伸呼叫這隻青蛙。
#e The dog whose head had been inserted inside the container also headed out.
#c 狗也跟著往外伸出頭, 牠的頭是在瓶子裡
#e The frog fell by the window.
#c 青蛙從窗戶掉下去。
#n 這句說者指的應該是'e av'u (狗)。
#e The boy went underneath the window and held the dog.
#c 男孩去窗戶底下抱起狗。
#e (The child) together with the dog, repeatedly called the frog.
#c 小孩跟狗在一起, 一直叫青蛙。
#e They went to look for (the frog) together.
#c 他們兩個一起去找青蛙。
#e At that time, the child headed into the hole and looked for the frog.
#c 那時候, 小孩頭伸進去洞裡找青蛙。
#e A mouse came out from the ground.
#c 一隻老鼠從地裡往外伸出(身體)。
#e (The mouse) did not like the child.
#c 那老鼠討厭那小孩。
#e The dog saw a bee(hive) hanging (down) and shook it.
#c 狗看見吊掛在樹上的蜂窩就搖那蜂窩。
#e The child climbed a tree and looked for the frog inside a hole.
#c 小孩爬上那棵樹，把頭伸進樹洞裡找青蛙。
#e When the child inserted (his head) into the hole,
#c 那時候這個小孩（頭）伸進洞裡面。
#e (It was) an owl (inside the tree).
#c 原來那個貓頭鷹在樹洞裡面。
#e The child got frightened and fell down.
#c 小孩嚇到了從樹上掉下來。
#e The dog shook the (beehive) and caused (the beehive) fall. The bees scattered and chased the dog.
#c 狗搖蜂窩，把(蜂窩)(搖了)掉下來，蜂四散飛，追那隻狗。
#e The owl hated the child.
#c 貓頭鷹討厭那小孩。
#e (The owl) chased (the boy) and wanted to peck at him.
#c 他一直追小孩想要啄他。
#e Then the child climbed a rock.
#c 後來小孩爬上一塊大石頭。
#e He went on calling the frog.
#c 他一直叫那青蛙。
#e The boy thought he was holding a branch, (but it turned out to be) a deer's antler.
#c 他抓著一個東西，他以為那是樹，原來是鹿的角。
#e The child got stuck between the deer's antlers. He was carried by the deer.
#c 那小孩卡在鹿的角上，鹿就帶著(孩子)跑。
#e The deer (took the child and) threw him over the cliff.
#c 那鹿(帶著小孩),把小孩摔落到懸崖。
#e The dog also fell down.
#c 狗也跟著掉下去。
#e The child and the dog fell into the water.
#c 小孩和狗剛好掉到水裡去。
#e The dog (sat) on the child's head. They floated toward where there was a tree.
#c 小狗（坐）在小孩的頭上，他們漂流到有樹的地方。

gloss: 助動詞.非主焦-3SG.屬格=完成

free: #e He told the dog not to speak. "Don't speak. (Be quiet.)"
#c 他叫那狗不要講話。"不要說話"。
#e He told the dog not to make any sound.
#c 他跟那隻狗說不要出聲音。
#e They climbed over a log. There was a hole in the log, and they peeked to the other side.
#c 他們爬上一個（倒下的）枯樹幹，上面有一個洞。他們探頭看枯樹的另一邊。
#e They saw two frogs together under the log.
#c 他們看見兩隻青蛙一起在枯樹底下。
#e After a while, they saw more frogs.
#c 過一會兒他們看到更多的青蛙。
#e (It was) like the two frogs' children, or relatives.
#c 像是那兩隻青蛙的小孩，要不然就是同類。
#n hoci no o'te 是定型化講法; 表示'還是;要不然'
#e The boy saw the frog which had belonged to him for a long time.
#c 男孩看到那原本是屬於他的青蛙。
#e He took (the frog) home.
#c 他拿著那青蛙帶牠回家。
#e The frogs lined up by the log and he took one frog (with him).
#c 其他的青蛙在枯樹上並排而坐，而他們就帶著那隻青蛙回家。
